article.headline: Evansville 58, S. Illinois 53
article.story:
ST. CHARLES, Mo. -- Shannon Novosel scored 18 points and Stephanie Bamberger added 13 as ninth-seeded Evansville defeated No. 8 Southern Illinois 58-53 in the first round of the Missouri Valley women's basketball tournament Thursday.

Evansville (12-18) went on a 15-4 run in the second half to pull away. Novosel sank a 3-pointer with 5:04 to give the Aces a 49-40 lead and Evansville expanded that lead to 55-44 with 1:33 left in the game.

Christine Presswood led the Salukis (9-19) with 15 points and Jasmine Gibson added 10.

Evansville made two field goals in the final 12:23 of the first half and Southern Illinois closed the period on a 12-4 run but the Salukis held just a 25-23 lead at halftime.
